==Awards== [[Bob Ward (football coach)|Bob Ward]] was named a first-team [[College Football All-America Team|All-American]] by the [[Associated Press]] and a second-team All-American by [[United Press]].<ref name="accaa">[http://grfx.cstv.com/photos/schools/acc/sports/m-footbl/auto_pdf/07fbguide173177.pdf ACC All-Americans] (PDF), ''2007 Atlantic Coast Conference Media Guide'', Atlantic Coast Conference, 2007, retrieved 16 January 2009.</ref> Ed Modzelewski was named an honorable mention All-American.<ref>[http://grfx.cstv.com/photos/schools/md/sports/m-footbl/auto_pdf/191-196.pdf All-Time Honors] (PDF), ''2001 Maryland Terrapins Football Media Guide'', CBS Sports, retrieved 8 December 2008.</ref> Pete Augsburger was named an honorable mention All-American by the United Press.<ref>''Terrapin'', University of Maryland Yearbook, Class of 1951, p. 277.</ref> Ward and [[Elmer Wingate]] were named All-Southern Conference.<ref name="socon">[http://www.soconsports.com/fls/4000/socon/files/07fbguide/record_book.pdf?SPSID=35576&SPID=1781&DB_OEM_ID=4000SoCon Records] (PDF), ''2007 Southern Conference Football Media Guide'', Southern Conference, p. 141â147, 2007, retrieved 6 October 2008.</ref>
